metadata.description:
Approaching two months of my hairloss cycle. üòÖWow what a journey!!! ü§ØI never thought I‚Äôd say this, BUT, I quite like being bald ü§≠. I‚Äôve had the most fabulous offers of hair loss systems from so many kind amazing places but For now I‚Äôve decided it‚Äôs not my time. I‚Äôm adapting to my new image, I‚Äôm loving doing my cardio and not having to wash my hair or worry about it getting greasy! Being able to chose what persona I want daily with the fabulous wigs available these days is so much fun, and less daunting now I know how to applicate and style them. Ive come to realise, I‚Äôm more confident in my own skin now than when I had hair!! I‚Äôve always been critical of myself, I‚Äôve always judged myself or wanted to change things.. strived for a perfection that DOESNT EXIST. Yet now I look in the mirror and I see a unique strong lady that I‚Äôm proud of and don‚Äôt want to change. It‚Äôs been the making of me, and I‚Äôm proud to walk along side so many amazing people in the hairloss community. If my hair comes back, amazing. Don‚Äôt get me wrong that would be the best outcome BUT If it doesn‚Äôt, I‚Äôve adapted, I‚Äôve grown with the loss of my hair and challenged myself to be a better person in the process. So whatever my outcome is, I‚Äôm prepared either way and truly thankful for the opportunities that have come from the loss of my hair. ‚ú®ü•ùI‚Äôm hoping to be able to organise hairloss retreats once it is safe for group gatherings. It would be so amazing to be able to meet others with hairloss and be able to introduce them to some of my contacts within the hairloss industry to help them like they‚Äôve helped me. Fingers crossed this will be possible sooner than later! Watch this space.. ü§ûüèΩüåüüíõ #alopeciaawareness #baldisbeautiful
